Thaumatococcus daniellii

   [10386.jpg]
    Authority   (Bennett) Benth.
      Family    Liliopsida:Zingiberidae:Zingiberales:Marantaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 10386

   Notes
   SOURCES (T. daniellii (Benn.) Benth.)
   Hackett C 1982 pp 54 [FER, PHO, DEP, PH, TEXT, TEMP]
   Duke J 1975 pp 29 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 410 [USE]
   GROWING PERIOD
   Herb.
   USE
   The pulp around the seed has a sweetening effect, it contains the taste
   modifying protein thaumatin. Its leafs are used for wrapping food and
   meat.
   COMMON NAMES
   Miracle-fruit, Katempe, Miraculous fruit, Katemfe.
   FURTHER INF
   It is a common plant which grows wild in forest clearings in many parts
   of Ghana. Fruits are traditinally collected from wild plants.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
